The following documents were submitted during the month of April to Government: Report on the labours in the bot. Garden and on the proceedings of the Gov. Botanist for March; return of expenditure during January, February & March;
M to J. O'Shanassy, 1 April 1858 and M to J. O'Shanassy, 31 March 1858. return of revenue for horses grazing at the reserve during the month of March; pay sheets showing an expenditure of 368£ 14/6d for salaries and wages;
letters not found. requisition for books and official formules, for ironfencing-material (supplied by the office of public works),
See M to C. Duffy, 14 April 1858 and T. Balmain to M, 30 April 1858 (in this edition as 58-04-30a). return of the officers of this department, requisition for the transit of Wardian Cases to Aukland,
Auckland. Moreton Bay and Honolulu, accounts for New Zealand plants = £24 5/,
letters not found. besides some minor official papers.
